WEBVTT

00:00.201 --> 00:01.472
PREVIOUS ON REAPER...

00:01.472 --> 00:03.104
BEFORE YOU WERE BORN,
YOUR MOM AND I

00:03.104 --> 00:04.305
SOLD YOUR SOUL
TO THE DEVIL.

00:04.305 --> 00:06.537
YOU SIGNED A CONTRACT
WITH THE DEVIL, SAM.

00:06.537 --> 00:07.738
FORGET ABOUT
THE CONTRACT.

00:07.738 --> 00:09.110
NO, I WANT TO SEE IT.

00:09.110 --> 00:10.581
WHAT IS IT ABOUT YOU, SAMMY?

00:10.581 --> 00:12.143
YOU JUST CAN'T SAY NO.

00:12.143 --> 00:16.187
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:16.187 --> 00:16.747
ALMOST READY?

00:16.747 --> 00:20.191
UH, YEAH, I JUST HAVE
TO LOCK UP, BUT I'LL
MEET YOU GUYS THERE.

00:20.191 --> 00:21.752
YOU'RE NOT GOING
TO CHICKEN OUT, ARE YOU?

00:21.752 --> 00:24.055
WHAT?
KARAOKE PERFORMANCE
ANXIETY.

00:24.055 --> 00:27.628
NO WAY. 4 BEERS DEEP,
I'LL BE ROCKING SOME
BOHEMIAN RHAPSODY.

00:27.628 --> 00:28.659
[LAUGHS]

00:28.659 --> 00:30.631
SERIOUSLY?
YEAH.

00:30.631 --> 00:32.603
OK, DON'T TAKE FOREVER,
ALL RIGHT?

00:32.603 --> 00:33.804
I'M NOT SINGING THAT
BY MYSELF.

00:33.804 --> 00:36.137
OK, I WON'T. 10 MINUTES.

00:36.137 --> 00:37.808
[IMITATING COCKING GUN]

00:37.808 --> 00:40.171
[IMITATING EXPLOSION]

00:49.080 --> 00:51.622
[RUMBLING]

01:02.093 --> 01:04.165
Sam: HELLO?

01:20.351 --> 01:22.853
IS ANYBODY HERE?

01:31.192 --> 01:33.824
[DOOR CREAKING]

01:38.129 --> 01:40.501
[THUD]

01:43.134 --> 01:46.337
OH. PLEASE,
STAY AWAY FROM ME.

01:50.110 --> 01:53.844
ARE YOU...SAM OLIVER?

01:53.844 --> 01:55.346
YEAH.

01:55.346 --> 01:57.848
I GOT A CONTRACT FOR YOU.

01:57.848 --> 01:58.889
WHAT?

01:58.889 --> 02:02.122
CONTRACT FOR YOUR SOUL.

02:02.122 --> 02:03.824
[GRUNTS]

02:03.824 --> 02:06.126
HEH, THAT'S...

02:06.897 --> 02:09.260
SIGN THERE. THERE.

02:09.260 --> 02:11.602
INITIAL THERE.

02:11.602 --> 02:13.734
THIS IS GONNA TAKE HOURS.
CAN IT WAIT?

02:13.734 --> 02:15.306
OF COURSE NOT.

02:15.306 --> 02:17.438
I JUST, UH, I HAD PLANS
WITH A GIRL.

02:17.438 --> 02:21.412
WE'RE MEETING
FOR KARAOKE
LIKE, RIGHT NOW.

02:21.412 --> 02:22.573
[LAUGHS] SO...

02:22.573 --> 02:24.445
HERE'S AN IDEA--
COME WITH.

02:24.445 --> 02:25.776
THE GIRLS ARE GONNA GET
REALLY WASTED,

02:25.776 --> 02:27.278
THEY'D BE ALL OVER
A GUY IN UNIFORM.

02:27.278 --> 02:29.650
I CAN HELP YOU OUT,
BE YOUR WING MAN.

02:29.880 --> 02:31.652
NOT--NOT TO SUGGEST
THAT YOU NEED ANY HELP.

02:31.652 --> 02:34.585
YOU'RE A VERY ATTRACTIVE
DEMON. HA HA.

02:34.585 --> 02:36.887
I'M--I'M NOT
HITTING ON YOU.

02:36.887 --> 02:39.690
I JUST...I'M GONNA
SHUT UP, I'M GONNA SIGN.

02:39.690 --> 02:40.891
THAT'S WHAT
I'M GONNA DO.

02:40.891 --> 02:43.334
I'M GONNA SIGN
RIGHT NOW.

02:45.766 --> 02:47.798
INITIAL.

02:48.369 --> 02:49.300
INITIAL.

02:49.300 --> 02:50.170
HALF-OFF JELLO SHOTS.

02:50.170 --> 02:52.743
JUST SAYIN',
JUST SAYIN'.

02:53.804 --> 02:55.876
DATE.

03:06.857 --> 03:09.720
[SNORING]

03:14.965 --> 03:16.727
[GAGGING]
OH!

03:16.727 --> 03:17.398
[COUGHING]

03:17.398 --> 03:19.430
WHAT HAPPENED TO YOU
LAST NIGHT?

03:19.430 --> 03:20.701
OH...

03:20.701 --> 03:24.275
I HAD TO SIGN DOCUMENTS
FOR LIKE 3 HOURS.

03:24.275 --> 03:25.205
REALLY?

03:25.205 --> 03:28.208
A DEMON DELIVERED
A COPY OF MY CONTRACT.

03:28.208 --> 03:30.210
HEY! [SLAPS LEG]
THAT'S GOOD, RIGHT?

03:30.210 --> 03:31.812
GOT THE COPY
OF YOUR CONTRACT,

03:31.812 --> 03:32.883
NOW YOU CAN, UH...

03:32.883 --> 03:34.615
WELL, I DON'T KNOW.
WHAT CAN YOU DO WITH THAT?

03:34.615 --> 03:36.887
I WAS HOPIN' I COULD
FIND A WAY OUT OF
WORKIN' FOR THE DEVIL,

03:36.887 --> 03:39.420
BUT I COULDN'T MAKE
HEADS OR TAILS OF IT.

03:39.420 --> 03:40.621
IT WAS HUGE.

03:40.621 --> 03:42.593
ALL LEGAL AND LATIN.

03:42.593 --> 03:44.224
WHOA!

03:44.224 --> 03:45.256
OH! OH, THAT HAD
TO HURT, HUH?

03:45.256 --> 03:48.799
I'VE NEVER SEEN
ANYBODY HIT THE FLOOR
THAT HARD IN MY LIFE.

03:48.799 --> 03:50.401
OH, OH!

03:50.401 --> 03:52.833
SON OF A BITCH!

03:52.833 --> 03:55.005
OH, IS IT SLIPPERY?

03:55.005 --> 03:57.007
MIGHT HAVE BEEN
SUCKING ON YOUR FEET
IN YOUR SLEEP.

03:57.007 --> 03:59.470
MY LITTLE BROTHER
DOES THAT.

04:12.953 --> 04:14.725
WHOA! [GROANING]

04:14.725 --> 04:17.558
ARE YOU SURE YOU DIDN'T
TIE ONE ON LAST NIGHT, MAN?

04:17.558 --> 04:18.359
YOU'RE A WRECK!

04:18.359 --> 04:19.490
YEAH, IT'S MY STUPID
DEMON-SENSE.

04:19.490 --> 04:22.763
EVEN WITH MY SHOES ON,
IT'S LIKE I'M WALKING
ON ICE.

04:22.763 --> 04:23.694
WHOA, WHOA.

04:23.694 --> 04:26.737
CAN I GET SOME HELP
HERE, PLEASE?

04:28.539 --> 04:30.571
YEAH.

04:39.650 --> 04:42.513
YES, AND FINE DAY
TO YOU, GOOD SIR.

04:42.513 --> 04:42.953
MM-HMM.

04:42.953 --> 04:45.886
SO, UH, WHAT'D
I MISS LAST NIGHT?

04:45.886 --> 04:47.518
OH, DUDE, THE BAR
WAS AWESOME,

04:47.518 --> 04:49.019
WE HAD A GREAT TIME.

04:49.019 --> 04:50.290
YEAH?
YEAH.

04:50.290 --> 04:50.961
WHAT HAPPENED?

04:50.961 --> 04:53.624
UH, NOTHING HAPPENED.
IT WAS SUPER BORING.

04:53.624 --> 04:54.765
SUCKED.

04:54.765 --> 04:55.996
YOU JUST SAID IT WAS AWESOME.

04:55.996 --> 04:58.068
YEAH, I CHOSE
MY WORDS POORLY, SAM.

04:58.068 --> 04:58.899
FORGET IT.

04:58.899 --> 05:00.901
WHAT HAPPENED AT THE BAR?

05:00.901 --> 05:01.572
I CAN'T TELL YOU.

05:01.572 --> 05:04.705
[SCOFFS] LOOK, SOCK,
I'M GONNA FIND OUT ANYWAY,

05:04.705 --> 05:07.478
SO JUST TELL ME
WHAT THE HELL HAPPENED!

05:07.478 --> 05:09.410
JUST, UM...

05:09.410 --> 05:10.310
OH, OH.

05:10.310 --> 05:12.683
OK, DO YOU REALLY
WANT TO KNOW WHAT
YOU MISSED LAST NIGHT?

05:12.683 --> 05:14.084
YEAH.
YEAH?

05:14.084 --> 05:16.447
YES.
THAT.

05:16.447 --> 05:17.618
GREG.

05:17.618 --> 05:21.652
WE WERE ALL WAITING
THERE FOR YOU AT THE BAR
FOR HOURS, BY THE WAY,

05:21.652 --> 05:24.395
AND THEN IN WALKS GREG
WITH HIS SUPER FANCY HAIR

05:24.395 --> 05:25.856
AND HIS POINTY SHOES,

05:25.856 --> 05:26.997
AND HE STARTS BUYING
EVERYBODY DRINKS.

05:26.997 --> 05:29.029
YOU LET HIM
BUY YOU A DRINK?

05:29.029 --> 05:30.731
I DON'T WANT YOU
TO THINK ABOUT THAT
RIGHT NOW, OK?

05:30.731 --> 05:32.963
I WANT YOU TO THINK
ABOUT GREG AND ANDI.

05:32.963 --> 05:34.034
GREG AND ANDI WHAT?

05:34.034 --> 05:36.567
THEY WERE HANGING OUT
TOGETHER...

05:36.567 --> 05:39.339
ON THE COUCH,
TALKING.

05:39.339 --> 05:41.972
AND THEY WERE THERE
UNTIL AFTER I WENT HOME.

05:41.972 --> 05:42.773
YEAH.

05:42.773 --> 05:44.715
I KNOW.
THEY OUTLASTED EVEN ME.

05:44.715 --> 05:46.817
ALL RIGHT,
YOU DON'T NEED
TO SEE THAT ANYMORE.

05:46.817 --> 05:48.919
DON'T LOOK.

05:49.980 --> 05:52.553
LOOK, YOU CAN'T LET THAT
GET YOU DOWN, ALL RIGHT?

05:52.553 --> 05:53.984
YOU HAVE DEVIL BUSINESS
TO TAKE CARE OF.

05:53.984 --> 05:56.557
I KNOW, IT'S JUST
ANDI THINKS
I BLEW HER OFF.

05:56.557 --> 05:59.890
I LOOK LIKE A JERK.
A JERK WITH TAPE
ON HIS SHOES.

05:59.890 --> 06:00.991
ALL RIGHT, LISTEN TO ME.

06:00.991 --> 06:03.494
I'M NOT ADVOCATING
VIOLENCE HERE,

06:03.494 --> 06:06.066
BUT IF YOU NEED TO, UH,

06:06.066 --> 06:07.838
TAKE CARE OF GREG,

06:07.838 --> 06:09.369
I KNOW SOME PEOPLE.

06:09.369 --> 06:10.571
YEAH, I KNOW THE DEVIL.

06:10.571 --> 06:13.544
I THINK MY PEOPLE
TRUMP YOUR PEOPLE.

06:14.004 --> 06:15.906
YEAH, UH-HUH.

06:15.906 --> 06:18.549
THAT'S GOOD.

06:18.549 --> 06:20.981
[MUSIC PLAYING]

06:27.758 --> 06:32.062
♪ WASTED ALL MY TIME
'CAUSE IT WON'T CONVINCE YOU ♪

06:32.062 --> 06:33.163
♪ YOU TEASE ME ♪

06:33.163 --> 06:35.065
♪ YOU TEASE ME ♪

06:35.065 --> 06:36.697
♪ BUT IT'S NOT JUST DOUBT ♪

06:36.697 --> 06:39.970
♪ NOW I'M MAKING UP
A TOWN TO BREATHE IN ♪

06:39.970 --> 06:41.602
WHAT IS TED DOING?

06:41.602 --> 06:43.634
I PUT A NOTE
ON HIS WINDSHIELD.

06:43.634 --> 06:45.806
IT SAYS, "SORRY,
I HIT YOUR CAR."

06:45.806 --> 06:48.008
YOU HIT TED'S CAR?
NOPE.

06:48.008 --> 06:48.909
WHO DID?
NO ONE.

06:48.909 --> 06:52.813
HE'S BEEN LOOKING
FOR THE DAMAGE
OVER 10 MINUTES NOW.

06:52.813 --> 06:55.486
[LAUGHS]
THAT'S GENIUS.

06:55.486 --> 06:58.048
YEAH, I THINK TED
WOULD USE A DIFFERENT WORD.

06:58.048 --> 06:59.890
HEY, TED.

06:59.890 --> 07:01.051
WHAT HAPPENED
TO YOUR CAR?

07:01.051 --> 07:02.793
DO YOU SEE SOMETHING?
YEAH.

07:02.793 --> 07:04.054
IT'S A LITTLE
CROOKED RIGHT THERE.

07:04.054 --> 07:05.425
YEAH, I SEE IT, TOO.

07:05.425 --> 07:07.197
IT'S DEFINITELY CROOKED.

07:07.197 --> 07:08.128
DAMN IT!

07:08.128 --> 07:09.900
I'M CALLING THIS NUMBER.

07:09.900 --> 07:11.131
WHO'S NUMBER
DID YOU PUT?

07:11.131 --> 07:13.163
REGIONAL MANAGER'S.

07:13.163 --> 07:15.466
NICE.

07:15.466 --> 07:16.837
SO...

07:16.837 --> 07:18.609
ANOTHER NO-SHOW LAST NIGHT.

07:18.609 --> 07:20.571
IT'S BECOMING A HABIT, SAM.

07:20.571 --> 07:24.444
YEAH, YEAH.
I KNOW, I KNOW,
I'M SORRY.

07:24.444 --> 07:27.017
PLEASE, JUST TELL ME
WHAT'S GOING ON WITH YOU.

07:27.017 --> 07:29.520
I JUST--I HAD
SOME STUFF.

07:29.520 --> 07:31.522
SOME STUFF. WHAT STUFF?

07:33.484 --> 07:35.886
JOGGING, ACTUALLY.

07:35.886 --> 07:37.488
UH, UH, LATE NIGHT
JOGGING.

07:37.488 --> 07:40.190
I'M GETTING IN SHAPE
FOR A TRIATHLON.

07:40.190 --> 07:41.962
OH. OK, SAM.

07:41.962 --> 07:44.765
YOU KNOW WHAT, YOU DON'T
HAVE TO TELL ME ANYTHING
ABOUT YOUR PERSONAL LIFE.

07:44.765 --> 07:46.937
JUST DON'T INSULT ME.

07:46.937 --> 07:47.638
NO, I'M NOT! I--

07:47.638 --> 07:48.999
YOU KNOW WHAT,
MY BREAK'S OVER.

07:48.999 --> 07:51.001
I'LL TALK TO YOU LATER.

07:51.942 --> 07:53.904
Ted: OH, YOU'RE THE IDIOT
THAT HIT MY CAR!

07:53.904 --> 07:56.046
I WANT YOUR NAME!

07:57.047 --> 07:58.078
YES, SIR.

07:58.078 --> 08:01.051
NO, SIR, I--I AM
ABSOLUTELY NOT DRUNK.

08:01.051 --> 08:05.055
THANK YOU FOR YOUR CONCERN
ABOUT MY MENTAL HEALTH, SIR.

08:07.518 --> 08:09.920
[SIGHS]

08:09.920 --> 08:12.593
Man: SAM...

08:19.900 --> 08:22.733
[ECHOING] SAM...

08:32.012 --> 08:34.084
BOO!

08:34.084 --> 08:35.646
[CHUCKLING]

08:35.646 --> 08:37.247
ALWAYS A GOOD EFFECT.

08:37.247 --> 08:40.891
LOW-TECH, BUT AWESOME RESULTS.

08:40.891 --> 08:43.023
I REALLY...

08:43.023 --> 08:44.555
DON'T CARE FOR YOU.

08:44.555 --> 08:47.297
OH, COME ON, SAMMY.
DON'T BE LIKE THAT.

08:47.297 --> 08:49.860
HEY, HOW'S THAT GAL
OF YOURS, HUH?

08:49.860 --> 08:50.961
EVERYTHING OK THERE?

08:50.961 --> 08:51.962
YOU KNOW ANDI'S
NOT MY "GAL."

08:51.962 --> 08:53.964
I HAD TO BAIL
ON HER AGAIN
LAST NIGHT.

08:53.964 --> 08:54.865
I'M SICK OF IT.

08:54.865 --> 08:56.637
SHE KNOWS
I'M LYING TO HER.

08:56.637 --> 08:57.107
OH, I SEE.

08:57.107 --> 08:59.570
AND NOW SHE'S SEEKING
COMFORT ELSEWHERE.

08:59.570 --> 09:01.541
WHAT'S HIS NAME? GREG?

09:01.541 --> 09:04.675
WELL, WE CAN DEAL WITH GREG
WHEN THE TIME COMES.

09:04.675 --> 09:05.676
NO PROBLEM.

09:05.676 --> 09:06.817
NO, LET'S NOT
DEAL WITH GREG.

09:06.817 --> 09:08.619
LET'S...
LET'S JUST DO THIS.

09:08.619 --> 09:11.021
OH, SURE. YOU WANT
TO BE ALL BUSINESS?
YEAH.

09:11.021 --> 09:11.852
WE CAN BE THAT WAY.

09:11.852 --> 09:14.785
WE'LL BE ALL BUSINESS,
HERE YOU GO.

09:15.025 --> 09:16.887
NOW THIS SWEET-FACED
MOTHER OF TWO

09:16.887 --> 09:20.931
WAS A P.T.A. LEADER,
AVID GARDNER, LOCAL ACTIVIST.

09:20.931 --> 09:22.963
HMM. SOME SMILE, HUH?

09:22.963 --> 09:24.895
LET ME GUESS--
SHE'S DEAD?

09:24.895 --> 09:26.897
YEP. SLIPPED AND FELL.

09:26.897 --> 09:29.770
CRACKED HER PRETTY HEAD OPEN
ON A TOILET.

09:29.770 --> 09:33.674
IN MY OPINION, A VERY
UNDIGNIFIED WAY TO GO.

09:34.004 --> 09:36.907
THIS BRIGHT-EYED,
INTREPID LOCAL REPORTER

09:36.907 --> 09:38.979
TOOK A HEADER
DOWN A STAIRWELL.

09:38.979 --> 09:42.112
SNAPPED HIS SPINE CLEAN
RIGHT AT THE NECK.

09:42.112 --> 09:45.115
ANOTHER ACCIDENTAL DEATH,
ACCORDING TO THE AUTHORITIES.

09:45.115 --> 09:47.988
A SOUL KILLED
ALL THESE PEOPLE.

09:47.988 --> 09:50.360
MADE IT LOOK LIKE
ACCIDENTS.

09:50.360 --> 09:51.962
AND MORE WILL DIE.

09:51.962 --> 09:52.923
WELL, WHO ARE THEY?

09:52.923 --> 09:55.666
AND--AND WHY
ARE WE DOWN HERE
IN THE SEWER?

09:55.666 --> 09:59.199
OH, COME ON.
FIRE UP THAT SLEEPING BEAN
OF YOURS, SAMMY.

09:59.199 --> 10:00.771
I CAN'T DO ALL THE WORK.

10:00.771 --> 10:01.802
I'M NOT ASKING
FOR ALL THE WORK.

10:01.802 --> 10:04.875
I JUST--I WANT
A CLUE THAT'S
REMOTELY HELPFUL.

10:04.875 --> 10:05.706
FINE.

10:05.706 --> 10:08.779
YOU WANT IT EASY?
I'LL MAKE IT EASY.

10:08.779 --> 10:11.111
I'LL POINT THE WAY.

10:12.913 --> 10:16.887
THAT'S FUNNY, HILARIOUS!
YOU'RE A JOKESTER!

10:16.887 --> 10:18.819
DICK.

10:18.819 --> 10:20.991
WHOA!

11:07.768 --> 11:10.070
WHOA, LOOK OUT!

11:10.070 --> 11:13.103
[TIRES SQUEALING]

11:37.998 --> 11:40.871
[SLIME SQUISHING]

12:02.092 --> 12:04.094
Sam: THE CAR LOST
CONTROL IN THE SLIME
AND CRASHED.

12:04.094 --> 12:06.897
IT WAS AWFUL.
GUY DIDN'T EVEN
HAVE A CHANCE.

12:06.897 --> 12:08.298
AND YOU SAID HE WAS
A LAWYER, RIGHT?

12:08.298 --> 12:09.199
YEAH, ED FAZIO.

12:09.199 --> 12:10.100
I'VE TRIED
CALLING HIS OFFICE,

12:10.100 --> 12:11.261
BUT I GUESS
THEY SHUT DOWN
AFTER THE NEWS.

12:11.261 --> 12:12.863
ALL RIGHT, LET'S TALK
CONSISTENCY HERE.

12:12.863 --> 12:14.434
WE'RE TALKING ABOUT A DUDE
MADE FROM SLIME.

12:14.434 --> 12:18.909
WHAT IS IT, SNOT-LIKE?
SPIT? HOUSEHOLD SLIME, WHAT?

12:18.909 --> 12:20.070
UH, HOUSEHOLD SLIME?

12:20.070 --> 12:22.773
COME ON, BEN, EVERYBODY KNOWS
WHAT HOUSEHOLD SLIME IS.
GIVE ME A BREAK.

12:22.773 --> 12:23.914
WELL, WHATEVER IT IS,
THERE BETTER BE

12:23.914 --> 12:26.947
SOMETHING BAD-ASS
IN THIS BOX TO HELP US
CATCH IT.

12:26.947 --> 12:29.149
Ben: UH-HUH.

12:35.255 --> 12:37.757
Ben: OH, WOW.

12:37.757 --> 12:39.389
DID THE DEVIL GIVE YOU THAT,
OR MY GRANDMOTHER?

12:39.389 --> 12:43.333
YEAH, MAYBE YOU WEAR THAT,
AND THE SOUL LAUGHS ITSELF
BACK TO HELL.

12:43.333 --> 12:43.864
HEH.

12:43.864 --> 12:45.065
LOOK, WE HAVE TO BACK
AND FIND THIS THING,
ALL RIGHT?

12:45.065 --> 12:48.238
LAST TIME I SAW IT,
IT WAS HEADING DOWN
INTO A SEWER GRATE.

12:48.238 --> 12:49.039
NO.

12:49.039 --> 12:50.971
NOT GOING DOWN
INTO THE SEWER.

12:50.971 --> 12:52.442
I JUST BOUGHT THESE PANTS.

12:52.442 --> 12:53.904
LOOK, THE SEWER'S
ALL WE GOT,

12:53.904 --> 12:55.846
SO SUCK IT UP,
YOU GUYS, WE'RE GOING.

12:55.846 --> 12:58.378
[KNOCK ON DOOR]

12:58.378 --> 12:59.049
DAD.

12:59.049 --> 13:02.012
MR. O, YOU'RE LOOKING
VERY PIMP TODAY.

13:02.012 --> 13:03.914
UH, THANK YOU, SOCK.

13:03.914 --> 13:05.015
UH-HUH.
HEY, BEN.

13:05.015 --> 13:07.187
HEY, MR. OLIVER.
SAM, I'LL CATCH YOU OUTSIDE.

13:07.187 --> 13:09.059
ALL RIGHT, COOL.

13:09.059 --> 13:10.420
EVERYTHING OK?

13:10.420 --> 13:11.261
YEAH, YEAH.

13:11.261 --> 13:14.064
I FOUND THIS
LYING ON THE FLOOR
AT HOME.

13:14.064 --> 13:16.296
THOUGHT YOU MIGHT NEED IT.

13:16.296 --> 13:17.968
OH, YEAH, THANK YOU.

13:17.968 --> 13:19.129
I, UH, FELL DOWN
A FEW TIMES.

13:19.129 --> 13:21.401
IT MUST HAVE POPPED OUT
OF MY POCKET.

13:22.172 --> 13:23.333
UH...

13:23.333 --> 13:26.076
SAM, WHAT IS THAT?

13:28.308 --> 13:30.380
THAT...

13:30.380 --> 13:32.512
IS THE CONTRACT.

13:33.183 --> 13:35.045
THE CONTRACT, HUH?

13:35.045 --> 13:37.587
YOU MEAN THE CONTRACT?

13:39.019 --> 13:41.091
WOW.

13:41.521 --> 13:44.294
YEAH, YEAH, WELL...

13:45.195 --> 13:46.396
SHOULD TAKE ME ABOUT A YEAR
TO GET THROUGH IT.

13:46.396 --> 13:49.359
WELL, YOU WANT ME
TO TAKE A LOOK AT IT
FOR YOU?

13:49.359 --> 13:50.060
NO, DAD, I CAN HANDLE IT.

13:50.060 --> 13:53.563
UH, ARE YOU SURE?
MAYBE THERE'S A WAY
I CAN HELP OUT.

13:53.563 --> 13:56.967
I--I GOTTA GET GOING.
GUYS ARE WAITING.

13:56.967 --> 13:59.269
YEAH.

13:59.269 --> 14:01.541
DAMN IT.

14:02.042 --> 14:04.344
DAD, WHAT--WHAT'S WRONG?

14:04.344 --> 14:06.276
AH, JUST SEEING
THAT CONTRACT

14:06.276 --> 14:08.148
JUST BROUGHT BACK
A FLOOD OF MEMORIES

14:08.148 --> 14:10.480
AND FEELINGS OF GUILT
FOR WHAT I DID TO YOU.

14:10.480 --> 14:12.122
NO, IT'S--IT'S OK.

14:12.122 --> 14:12.953
WELL, LOOK AT ME, SAM.

14:12.953 --> 14:15.585
I'M STANDING IDLE
WHILE YOU CARRY
THE BURDEN FOR THIS.

14:15.585 --> 14:17.627
WHAT KIND OF FATHER
DOES THAT?

14:17.627 --> 14:22.262
I WANT YOU TO ARRANGE
A MEETING WITH ME
AND THE DEVIL.

14:22.262 --> 14:23.863
WHAT? WHY?

14:23.863 --> 14:26.636
TO TALK TO HIM.
TO CONVINCE HIM
TO RELEASE YOUR SOUL,

14:26.636 --> 14:27.167
TO MAKE A TRADE.

14:27.167 --> 14:30.941
TRADE? DAD, I DON'T
THINK YOU HAVE
ANYTHING TO TRADE.

14:30.941 --> 14:31.401
I HAVE SKILLS, SAM.

14:31.401 --> 14:34.975
ALL THE YEARS IN ADVERTISING,
I CAN USE THOSE SKILLS.

14:34.975 --> 14:38.048
I DON'T--I JUST DON'T
THINK YOU HAVE ANYTHING
THE DEVIL NEEDS.

14:38.048 --> 14:42.082
I'VE CREATED CARTOON MASCOTS
TO SELL CIGARETTES TO KIDS, SAM.

14:42.082 --> 14:43.283
TO KIDS.

14:43.283 --> 14:44.654
TELL THE DEVIL THAT.

14:44.654 --> 14:46.156
THAT'S A GOOD POINT.

14:46.156 --> 14:48.318
YEAH. GET ME THAT MEETING.

14:48.318 --> 14:51.421
OK, I'LL...I'LL ASK.

14:51.421 --> 14:53.363
OK, GOOD, GOOD.

14:59.369 --> 15:01.901
HEY. NICE FLOWERS.

15:01.901 --> 15:02.933
HEY. YEAH.

15:02.933 --> 15:05.275
IT'S KIND OF
A NICE SURPRISE.

15:05.275 --> 15:08.038
OH, YOU GOT A...CARD.

15:08.038 --> 15:09.039
OH.

15:09.039 --> 15:11.011
FLOWERS, SAM?

15:11.011 --> 15:13.083
VERY INAPPROPRIATE.

15:13.083 --> 15:15.045
MAKE YOUR CO-WORKER
UNCOMFORTABLE,

15:15.045 --> 15:16.246
YOU AMP UP
THE TENSION.

15:16.246 --> 15:18.088
AND WE HAVHARASSMENT
SEXUAL HARRASMENT
RULES

15:18.088 --> 15:22.022
THAT CLEARLY FORBID
THESE TYPES OF
UNWANTED OVERTURES.

15:22.022 --> 15:23.393
I'M NOT HARASSING, TED.
SAM?

15:23.393 --> 15:25.295
YEAH.
JUST TRYING
TO PROTECT YOU.

15:25.295 --> 15:26.596
FLOWERS AREN'T FROM ME, TED.

15:26.596 --> 15:28.098
NO, THEY'RE FROM GREG.

15:28.098 --> 15:29.529
GREG. I MET HIM.

15:29.529 --> 15:32.432
WE HAD A CONVERSATION
ABOUT CEILING FANS.

15:32.432 --> 15:35.235
I HEARTILY APPROVE.

15:35.235 --> 15:35.935
[SCOFFS]

15:35.935 --> 15:37.467
THAT'S FUNNY,
HIM GIVING ME
FLOWERS.

15:37.467 --> 15:41.341
THEY'RE--THEY'RE REALLY NICE.

15:41.341 --> 15:42.042
YEAH.

15:42.042 --> 15:44.314
WOW. NOT AS NICE
AS THAT SWEATER, THOUGH.

15:44.314 --> 15:46.476
WHAT HAPPENED?
DID YOU LOSE A BET?

15:46.476 --> 15:47.717
OH...

15:47.717 --> 15:49.449
UH, YEAH.

15:49.449 --> 15:50.420
YOU GOIN' SOMEWHERE?

15:50.420 --> 15:54.554
I GOT A FAMILY THING
THAT I GOT...

15:54.554 --> 15:56.586
WHATEVER.

15:56.586 --> 16:00.991
[SIGHS] ANDI,
WAIT, LISTEN.

16:02.062 --> 16:05.095
OK, I HAVEN'T BEEN
100% HONEST WITH YOU.

16:05.095 --> 16:07.367
WHAT'S GOING ON, SAM?

16:08.038 --> 16:10.640
I-I HAVE SOME STUFF
THAT I NEED TO TELL YOU.

16:10.640 --> 16:13.073
OBVIOUSLY,
SO JUST TELL ME.

16:13.073 --> 16:14.004
OK--
AHEM!

16:14.004 --> 16:16.146
YEAH. OK, I CAN'T RIGHT NOW.

16:16.146 --> 16:18.548
BUT I WILL.
TONIGHT, I PROMISE.

16:18.548 --> 16:19.979
UH, 7:00?

16:19.979 --> 16:20.680
ALL RIGHT.

16:20.680 --> 16:21.481
OK, I'LL PICK YOU UP,

16:21.481 --> 16:24.014
AND I WILL--
I'LL TELL YOU
EVERYTHING, OK?

16:24.014 --> 16:26.216
EVERYTHING.

16:26.216 --> 16:27.287
[THUD]

16:27.287 --> 16:30.160
I'M--I'M GOOD.

16:30.160 --> 16:31.421
OK.

16:31.421 --> 16:34.064
[MUSIC PLAYING]

16:34.394 --> 16:36.396
♪ SO PRETTY,
SO PRETTY ♪

16:36.396 --> 16:38.268
♪ SO PRETTY, OH, OH, OH ♪

16:38.268 --> 16:39.329
♪ SO PRETTY, SO PRETTY ♪

16:39.329 --> 16:42.332
♪ SO PRETTY, OH, OH, OH ♪

16:42.332 --> 16:44.003
SO THAT'S WHERE I SAW
FAZIO CRASH,

16:44.003 --> 16:45.004
RIGHT OVER THERE.

16:45.004 --> 16:47.577
THE SLIME GUY WENT DOWN
THE SEWAGE RIGHT HERE.

16:47.577 --> 16:50.009
ALL RIGHT.

16:54.414 --> 16:56.786
Ben: CAREFUL, GUYS.

16:57.787 --> 17:00.620
All: WHOA, WHOA!

17:00.620 --> 17:01.351
HOLY...

17:01.351 --> 17:03.693
SORRY, GUYS,
THIS IS THE ONLY WAY.

17:03.693 --> 17:05.155
ALL RIGHT, HERE.

17:05.155 --> 17:07.097
UGH.

17:07.097 --> 17:09.799
IT SMELLS LIKE STRAWBERRY.

17:09.799 --> 17:12.802
OH, YEAH.
THAT'S GOOD.

17:12.802 --> 17:14.464
YEAH.
ALL RIGHT.

17:14.464 --> 17:17.167
ALL RIGHT.
ALL RIGHT, I'LL GO.

17:22.272 --> 17:24.374
SORRY.

17:28.518 --> 17:31.121
SO I'M GONNA TELL ANDI.

17:31.121 --> 17:33.253
TELL ANDI WHAT?

17:33.253 --> 17:35.085
EVERYTHING.

17:35.085 --> 17:36.086
WHOA, WHAT EVERYTHING?

17:36.086 --> 17:39.329
EVERYTHING, EVERYTHING.
ABOUT THIS, ABOUT WORKING
FOR THE DEVIL.

17:39.329 --> 17:41.691
ARE YOU CRAZY? WHY?

17:41.691 --> 17:42.262
BECAUSE I HAVE TO.

17:42.262 --> 17:45.064
SHE'S ALREADY MAD AT ME
BECAUSE SHE THINKS
I'M A LIAR,

17:45.064 --> 17:47.167
WHICH I AM, AND I CAN'T KEEP
COMING UP WITH EXCUSES

17:47.167 --> 17:48.338
EVERY TIME I HAVE
TO RUN ERRANDS
FOR THE DEVIL.

17:48.338 --> 17:52.502
IF I'M EVER GONNA HAVE
A CHANCE WITH ANDI,
I GOTTA COME CLEAN.

17:52.502 --> 17:53.703
OH, SHE'S GONNA
FREAK OUT, MAN.

17:53.703 --> 17:54.804
SHE'S GONNA THINK
YOU'RE OFF YOUR NUT.

17:54.804 --> 17:57.447
YEAH, WELL, I'M PRETTY SURE
SHE ALREADY THINKS THAT.

17:57.447 --> 17:59.849
HEY.

17:59.849 --> 18:02.081
HEY, LOOK AT THAT.

18:02.081 --> 18:04.454
WAIT, THAT'S HIM,
THAT'S THE SOUL,
THAT'S GOTTA BE.

18:04.454 --> 18:05.715
LOOK, LOOK, FOOTPRINTS.

18:05.715 --> 18:08.618
I THINK HE'S DOWN HERE.

18:17.096 --> 18:19.729
Sock: OH, BOY.

18:24.474 --> 18:26.776
[GROANING]

18:28.138 --> 18:30.140
WHAT IS THIS?

18:30.140 --> 18:31.711
Sam: LOOKS LIKE
A POLITICAL FUNDRAISER.

18:31.711 --> 18:34.814
SOUL COULD BE TRYING
TO ATTACK SOMEBODY HERE.

18:34.814 --> 18:36.646
HELL, OR IT
LIVES HERE.

18:36.646 --> 18:37.817
[FLY BUZZING]

18:37.817 --> 18:38.848
OH, MY GOD, LOOK.

18:38.848 --> 18:40.790
Sam: WHAT?
HOLD UP.

18:40.790 --> 18:42.752
I SEE AN OPEN BAR.

18:42.752 --> 18:44.294
HI, HOW YOU DOIN'?

18:44.294 --> 18:44.824
GOOD DRINKS?

18:44.824 --> 18:47.527
OH, 25-YEAR-OLD SCOTCH.
I'M GOIN' IN.

18:47.527 --> 18:48.298
NO, NO, NO, NO.

18:48.298 --> 18:49.859
ONE OF THESE PEOPLE
MIGHT BE THE SOUL.

18:49.859 --> 18:51.130
CLEARLY, YOU DIDN'T HEAR ME.

18:51.130 --> 18:52.302
25-YEAR-OLD SCOTCH,
GOIN' IN.

18:52.302 --> 18:53.463
PPHHBTT!
GENTLEMEN.

18:53.463 --> 18:54.404
HEY.
HI.

18:54.404 --> 18:55.465
HI, CAN I HELP YOU?

18:55.465 --> 18:58.508
THIS A BY DONATION ONLY EVENT.

18:58.508 --> 19:00.410
AH. WHAT A COINCIDENCE,
ACTUALLY,

19:00.410 --> 19:03.443
BECAUSE I HAVE BEEN LOOKING
TO DONATE A BUNCH OF MONEY

19:03.443 --> 19:04.674
TO A WORTHY CANDIDATE.
[STAMMERING]

19:04.674 --> 19:07.517
SAM. NOW, LISTEN,
I HAVE A COUPLE
PRESSING CONCERNS.

19:07.517 --> 19:11.381
UM, WHAT IS YOUR STANDPOINT
ON LEGALIZING PROSTITUTION?

19:11.381 --> 19:13.753
I'LL HANDLE THIS,
MR. HARTFORD.

19:13.753 --> 19:16.186
Sock: THANK YOU.
ARE YOU THE PROSTITUTION GUY?

19:16.186 --> 19:18.488
WE'RE FRIENDS WITH ED.

19:19.189 --> 19:20.890
ED FAZIO.

19:20.890 --> 19:22.832
AH. WELL, IN THAT CASE.

19:22.832 --> 19:27.197
GET THE HELL OFF MY PROPERTY
BEFORE I CALL THE POLICE.

19:27.767 --> 19:28.368
OK.

19:28.368 --> 19:30.800
JERRY, WILL YOU
TAKE CARE OF THIS, PLEASE?

19:30.800 --> 19:31.701
AHEM.

19:31.701 --> 19:33.843
ED FAZIO IS DEAD.

19:35.575 --> 19:37.407
HE DIED?

19:37.407 --> 19:38.848
YEAH, IN A CAR ACCIDENT.

19:38.848 --> 19:41.611
A FEW HOURS AGO.

19:41.611 --> 19:44.354
WELL, THAT IS A SHAME.

19:44.354 --> 19:46.816
THAT IS A CRYING SHAME.

19:47.817 --> 19:49.219
WELL, NOT FOR ME.

19:49.219 --> 19:50.560
BUT I'M SURE IF YOU LOOK
FAR ENOUGH,

19:50.560 --> 19:53.663
YOU'LL FIND A SAP OUT THERE
WHO DID LIKE THE GUY.

19:53.663 --> 19:55.765
HEH HEH, OK?
ALL RIGHT.

19:55.765 --> 19:57.367
JERRY.

19:58.568 --> 19:59.629
COME ON.

19:59.629 --> 20:01.931
YOU NEED TO LEAVE.

20:06.736 --> 20:08.978
HE DIDN'T EVEN CARE
ABOUT THE DEAD GUY.

20:08.978 --> 20:09.839
ABSOLUTELY NOT.

20:09.839 --> 20:11.641
IT'S LIKE HE WANTED
FAZIO DEAD,

20:11.641 --> 20:12.412
YOU KNOW WHAT I MEAN?

20:12.412 --> 20:13.483
YOU KNOW WHAT, I BET
HARTFORD IS THE SOUL.

20:13.483 --> 20:16.316
I DON'T KNOW.
I DIDN'T EVEN SEE
THE SLIME BAG'S FACE.

20:16.316 --> 20:18.388
WELL, ONLY ONE WAY
TO FIND OUT.

20:18.388 --> 20:21.251
WAIT, SOCK! SOCK!
STOP, SOCK!

20:21.251 --> 20:23.853
[ALL YELLING]

20:24.994 --> 20:26.456
SOCK! NO!

20:26.456 --> 20:28.328
[YELLING CONTINUES]

20:29.859 --> 20:30.960
WHOA!

20:30.960 --> 20:32.532
[SOCK GROANING]

20:32.532 --> 20:33.863
OK.

20:33.863 --> 20:35.905
IT'S COOL.

20:36.536 --> 20:38.768
HEY, DO YOU THINK
I CAN GET MY SWEATER BACK?
IT'S AN HEIRLOOM.

20:38.768 --> 20:42.011
MY DEAD GRANDMOTHER
MADE IT FOR ME, OK?!

21:07.367 --> 21:08.838
MY MOM'S GONNA
KILL ME.

21:08.838 --> 21:11.671
SHE COULD HANDLE US
BEING LOST
IN THE SEWERS.

21:11.671 --> 21:13.903
SHE COULD HANDLE THAT.

21:18.348 --> 21:18.908
WHAT ARE YOU DOIN'?

21:18.908 --> 21:21.851
WE GOTTA KICK
SOMEBODY'S ASS,
ESTABLISH DOMINANCE,

21:21.851 --> 21:22.952
OTHERWISE, UH...

21:22.952 --> 21:26.656
DELIVERANCE BRIDES,
YOU KNOW WHAT I MEAN?

21:26.656 --> 21:29.919
I CAN TAKE THIS GUY.
CHECK IT OUT.

21:35.825 --> 21:36.866
YO, HOMEBOY.

21:36.866 --> 21:38.928
WHAT ARE YOU IN FOR?

21:38.928 --> 21:41.831
TRIPLE HOMICIDE.

21:42.732 --> 21:45.375
TRIFECTA. NICE WORK.

21:45.375 --> 21:47.937
THAT'S GOOD.

21:50.680 --> 21:51.941
I THINK WE'RE
IN BIG TROUBLE.

21:51.941 --> 21:54.484
LOOK, WE HAVE MORE
IMPORTANT THINGS, ALL RIGHT?
WE LOST THE VESSEL,

21:54.484 --> 21:55.985
AND WE'RE NOT GOING TO GET
ANOTHER ONE BACK.

21:55.985 --> 21:58.648
AND THAT TRUMPS
PRISON RAPE?

21:59.419 --> 22:01.451
THERE. THAT'S THEM.

22:01.451 --> 22:02.592
UNBELIEVABLE.

22:02.592 --> 22:06.025
I KNEW YOU WOULDN'T
QUIT ME, BABY. I KNEW IT.

22:06.526 --> 22:08.358
MY BOSS CONVINCED
BOBBY HARTFORD

22:08.358 --> 22:09.959
NOT TO PRESS CHARGES
AGAINST YOU GUYS.

22:09.959 --> 22:13.833
BUT YOU HAVE TO PROMISE
TO NEVER GO NEAR HIM AGAIN.

22:13.833 --> 22:14.664
YOU MEAN,
HE JUST LET US GO?

22:14.664 --> 22:16.936
HARTFORD'S ABOUT TO
ANNOUNCE HIS CANDIDACY
FOR CITY COUNCIL,

22:16.936 --> 22:19.639
WHICH MEANS
HE DOESN'T WANT TO DEAL
WITH YOU GOOFBALLS.

22:19.639 --> 22:20.970
HAS HARTFORD BEEN HAVING
ANY PROBLEMS LATELY,

22:20.970 --> 22:22.872
LIKE WITH LAWYERS
OR SOMETHING?

22:22.872 --> 22:24.874
YEAH, HE'S ABOUT
TO GET HIS ASS SUED.

22:24.874 --> 22:25.945
REALLY? WHY?

22:25.945 --> 22:27.617
DUMPING TOXIC WASTE.

22:27.617 --> 22:28.818
HIS FAMILY OWNS
A CHEMICAL COMPANY.

22:28.818 --> 22:31.381
IT'S BEEN RUMORED
THAT THEY'VE BEEN
DUMPING FOR YEARS,

22:31.381 --> 22:32.822
BACK WHEN HIS DAD
WAS IN CHARGE.

22:32.822 --> 22:33.923
FINALLY GOT ENOUGH EVIDENCE
AGAINST HIM

22:33.923 --> 22:36.055
TO FILE A CLASS ACTION
THIS YEAR.

22:36.055 --> 22:38.127
HIS DAD?
YEP.

22:38.127 --> 22:40.660
BOBBY SENIOR.
TOO BAD HE'S DEAD.

22:40.660 --> 22:45.935
I WOULD LOVE TO SEE
THAT SLIMEBALL PAY,
JUST LIKE HIS SON.

22:48.838 --> 22:50.069
Sam: IT'S THE DAD,
IT'S GOTTA BE.

22:50.069 --> 22:50.870
Ben: WELL,
WHY COME BACK NOW?

22:50.870 --> 22:53.973
BOBBY JUNIOR'S RUNNING
FOR OFFICE AND THIS LAWSUIT
COULD RUIN HIM.

22:53.973 --> 22:55.475
DAD'S TRYING TO GET RID
OF HIS ENEMIES.

22:55.475 --> 22:57.146
WE GOTTA GET
THAT SWEATER BACK.

22:57.146 --> 22:58.047
YEAH.

22:58.047 --> 22:59.108
WAIT, WAIT, WAIT.

22:59.108 --> 23:00.880
IS THAT WHAT TIME IT IS?

23:00.880 --> 23:01.811
YEAH.

23:01.811 --> 23:03.583
DAMN IT, I'M 3 HOURS
LATE TO MEET ANDI!

23:03.583 --> 23:04.914
WELL, GO.
WE'LL FIND
THE VESSEL.

23:04.914 --> 23:06.486
HOW? YOU CAN'T
BREAK INTO HARTFORD'S!

23:06.486 --> 23:07.517
10 TO ONE, NOBODY KEPT
THAT UGLY SWEATER,

23:07.517 --> 23:09.959
IT'S IN THE TRASH.
HARTFORD'S HOUSE, ALL RIGHT?

23:09.959 --> 23:10.990
OK, I'LL MEET YOU GUYS THERE.

23:10.990 --> 23:11.991
YOU EVER DUMPSTER DIVE?

23:11.991 --> 23:14.664
OF COURSE. REMEMBER
THAT SHIRT I GOT YOU
FOR YOUR BIRTHDAY?

23:14.664 --> 23:17.396
THAT'S A FINE GRAB.

23:17.827 --> 23:20.700
[KNOCKS ON DOOR]

23:22.001 --> 23:24.073
OH.

23:24.073 --> 23:24.904
SAM.

23:24.904 --> 23:27.076
HI, MRS. PRENDERGAST.
IS ANDI HOME?

23:27.076 --> 23:28.608
NO, SHE WENT OUT.

23:28.608 --> 23:30.580
SHE GOT A CALL
FROM SOMEONE.

23:30.580 --> 23:32.011
A FRIEND.

23:32.011 --> 23:34.944
GREG. UH, SHE WENT OUT
WITH GREG? RIGHT, GREG?

23:34.944 --> 23:36.586
I THINK IT WAS GREG.

23:36.586 --> 23:37.887
OK. UM...

23:37.887 --> 23:41.791
DO YOU HAVE ANY IDEA
WHERE THEY MIGHT HAVE--NO?

23:41.791 --> 23:42.852
OH.

23:42.852 --> 23:44.494
UM, OK.

23:44.494 --> 23:45.625
SHE'LL PROBABLY
BE BACK SOON.

23:45.625 --> 23:48.097
WOULD YOU LIKE
TO COME IN AND WAIT?

23:48.698 --> 23:50.660
NO, NO, NO,
THANK YOU.

23:50.660 --> 23:51.901
UM, THAT'S OK.

23:51.901 --> 23:53.202
WELL, GOOD-NIGHT, SAM.

23:53.202 --> 23:55.204
GOOD-NIGHT.

23:59.438 --> 24:01.070
OH, GOD!

24:01.070 --> 24:03.743
[MUTTERING]

24:06.115 --> 24:08.818
SAY HI TO YOUR PARENTS
FOR ME, SAM.

24:08.818 --> 24:11.120
YEAH. OK. I'LL DO THAT.

24:11.120 --> 24:12.822
OK.
OK.

24:12.822 --> 24:14.824
SEE YA.
BYE.

24:18.127 --> 24:20.159
[SIGHS]

24:22.461 --> 24:24.594
SO, GREG...

24:24.594 --> 24:25.595
[SIGHS]

24:25.595 --> 24:26.966
WHAT ARE YOU
DOING HERE?

24:26.966 --> 24:28.968
WELL, I HAVE A SOLUTION
TO YOUR PROBLEM.

24:28.968 --> 24:31.841
I KNOW YOU'VE
BEEN DISTRACTED

24:31.841 --> 24:33.042
BY ALL THIS GREG BUSINESS,

24:33.042 --> 24:37.476
SO I TOOK THE LIBERTY
TO DIG UP SOME DIRT ON HIM.

24:37.476 --> 24:39.008
I'M NOT INTERESTED.

24:39.008 --> 24:40.910
OH, I THINK YOU'RE GOING
TO WANT TO SEE THIS.

24:40.910 --> 24:44.013
SEE, HE'S BEEN DATING
OTHER WOMEN.

24:44.013 --> 24:45.054
PLURAL.

24:45.054 --> 24:47.987
TWINS, TO BE EXACT.

24:47.987 --> 24:50.219
WHAT?

24:50.219 --> 24:51.561
HA.

24:51.561 --> 24:53.693
DIRTY GIRLS.

24:53.693 --> 24:54.564
SLUTTY.

24:54.564 --> 24:56.696
OH, THIS PLAYER
EVEN MAKES ME JEALOUS.

24:56.696 --> 24:59.098
I'LL JUST BET YOU
THAT ANDI WILL BE
VERY INTERESTED

24:59.098 --> 25:02.171
IN HEARING ABOUT THIS.

25:02.171 --> 25:03.833
NO.

25:03.833 --> 25:05.104
NO, NO, NO. I KNOW
WHAT YOU'RE DOING,

25:05.104 --> 25:06.205
YOU'RE TRYING
TO TEMPT ME,

25:06.205 --> 25:07.637
AND I'M NOT GOING
TO FALL FOR THAT.

25:07.637 --> 25:09.709
I'M NOT GONNA
STOOP THAT LOW.

25:09.709 --> 25:10.980
OK.

25:10.980 --> 25:12.642
WHAT'S YOUR PLAN, THEN?

25:12.642 --> 25:16.045
I DON'T KNOW.
I'LL JUST...

25:16.045 --> 25:17.947
I'LL OUTCHARM HIM.

25:17.947 --> 25:19.248
RIGHT.

25:19.248 --> 25:21.991
WELL, GOOD LUCK WITH THAT.

25:24.594 --> 25:25.094
WAIT.

25:25.094 --> 25:28.257
[SIGHS] I THINK
WE KNOW WHO
THE SOUL IS.

25:28.257 --> 25:29.629
HARTFORD'S DAD, RIGHT?

25:29.629 --> 25:30.860
HE DUMPED A BUNCH
OF TOXIC WASTE,

25:30.860 --> 25:32.732
AND NOW HE'S BACK
TO HELP HIS SON?

25:32.732 --> 25:33.232
YEAH, SAME OLD STORY.

25:33.232 --> 25:36.105
THE SINS OF THE FATHER
ARE VISITED ON THE SON.

25:36.105 --> 25:37.707
CIRCLE OF LIFE.

25:37.707 --> 25:40.009
OH, MY DAD,
RIGHT, UM...

25:40.009 --> 25:42.772
HE WANTS TO ARRANGE
A MEETING WITH YOU.

25:42.772 --> 25:43.542
NOT A CHANCE.

25:43.542 --> 25:45.575
HE JUST WANTS
TO MEET WITH YOU.

25:45.575 --> 25:46.115
HE ONLY WANTS
TO TALK.

25:46.115 --> 25:48.918
I ALREADY HAVE
EVERYTHING I NEED
FROM YOUR FATHER.

25:48.918 --> 25:51.050
HE HAS NOTHING ELSE
THAT I WANT.

25:51.050 --> 25:54.323
FEEL FREE TO PASS ALONG
THAT MESSAGE.

26:09.098 --> 26:10.940
HEY, CHECK THIS OUT.

26:10.940 --> 26:13.102
ED FAZIO WAS THE LAWYER
ON THE CASE

26:13.102 --> 26:15.304
AGAINST THE HARTFORD
FAMILY.

26:15.304 --> 26:16.946
HE'S PICTURED HERE
WITH THE REPORTER

26:16.946 --> 26:20.980
AND AN ACTIVIST
WHO HELPED BREAK OPEN
THE CASE.

26:21.611 --> 26:23.953
Sam: WHERE'D YOU GET THIS?

26:23.953 --> 26:26.155
OH, WE STOPPED AT A COMPUTER
AT A KINKOS ON THE WAY OVER.

26:26.155 --> 26:30.059
ACTUALLY, I GOT A RECEIPT
SO SATAN CAN REIMBURSE ME.

26:30.059 --> 26:33.192
THESE ARE THE PICTURES
THE DEVIL SHOWED ME.

26:33.192 --> 26:34.664
THEY'RE ALL DEAD.

26:34.664 --> 26:35.925
YEAH, AND IF
THEY'RE ALL DEAD,

26:35.925 --> 26:36.926
WHAT ABOUT
THE LAWSUIT?

26:36.926 --> 26:38.968
DOES IT DIE
WITH THEM?

26:38.968 --> 26:42.331
I DON'T KNOW, MAYBE.

26:45.735 --> 26:47.837
THIS IS WORSE
THAN SEWERS.

26:47.837 --> 26:49.378
I MEAN, HOW MANY CATS
DO THESE PEOPLE OWN?

26:49.378 --> 26:51.641
WELL, JUDGING BY THE AMOUNT
OF CAT LITTER,

26:51.641 --> 26:53.943
I'D SAY ABOUT 1,200.

26:53.943 --> 26:57.016
DAMN IT! STUPID...GARBAGE!

26:58.047 --> 26:59.318
[SIGHS]

26:59.318 --> 27:01.150
SO, UH...

27:01.150 --> 27:03.853
HOW'D IT GO WITH ANDI?

27:07.326 --> 27:09.128
NOT GOOD.

27:09.929 --> 27:12.201
SORRY, DUDE.

27:12.702 --> 27:14.103
ALL RIGHT, COME HERE.

27:14.103 --> 27:16.035
COME HERE, COME HERE.

27:16.035 --> 27:17.366
COME HERE.

27:17.366 --> 27:19.308
[SIGHS]

27:19.308 --> 27:21.210
IN THE ELEVENTH GRADE,

27:21.210 --> 27:25.044
I WAS IN LOVE WITH THIS GIRL
NAMED SUSAN PULITZER.

27:25.044 --> 27:28.017
I WAS CONVINCED
THAT SHE WAS THE ONE.

27:28.017 --> 27:32.221
AND THEN SHE CAME BACK
FROM SUMMER VACATION,

27:32.221 --> 27:35.224
AND SHE WAS...PREGNANT.

27:35.224 --> 27:37.656
I THOUGHT, GOOD.

27:37.656 --> 27:40.059
NOW I KNOW THAT SHE GOES
ALL THE WAY FOR SURE.

27:40.059 --> 27:44.333
THEN HER PARENTS SENT HER OFF
TO A CONVENT SCHOOL,

27:44.333 --> 27:46.065
AND, UH...

27:46.065 --> 27:48.968
I NEVER SAW HER
OR HEARD FROM HER AGAIN.

27:48.968 --> 27:51.941
I WAS ABSOLUTELY DEVASTATED.

27:51.941 --> 27:54.003
COMPLETELY.

27:54.003 --> 27:57.747
WELL, LOOK, I'M JUST TRYING
TO COMMISERATE HERE, OK?

27:57.747 --> 27:59.879
MAKE YOU FEEL
A LITTLE BETTER
ABOUT ANDI.

27:59.879 --> 28:02.111
SOME THINGS CAN'T BE HELPED.

28:02.111 --> 28:03.713
NO, I REFUSE
TO ACCEPT THAT.

28:03.713 --> 28:05.014
I'M NOT GONNA LET
ANDI JUST SLIP AWAY.

28:05.014 --> 28:07.086
ALL RIGHT, GOOD,
WELL, WHAT ARE YOU
GONNA DO, THEN?

28:07.086 --> 28:09.058
I DON'T KNOW.
I DON'T...

28:09.058 --> 28:10.960
SOMETHING.

28:11.821 --> 28:13.963
OH, LOOK, LOOK!
I FOUND IT!

28:13.963 --> 28:15.224
IT'S RIGHT HERE!

28:15.224 --> 28:16.365
YOU FOUND IT?

28:16.365 --> 28:17.266
IT'S STUCK.

28:17.266 --> 28:18.998
MOVE THE STUFF ON TOP.

28:18.998 --> 28:21.731
HURRY UP SO WE CAN GET
THE HELL OUT OF HERE.

28:21.731 --> 28:23.302
OK, HOW ABOUT A HAND,
PLEASE, BEN?

28:23.302 --> 28:24.904
HOLD ON, HOLD ON.

28:24.904 --> 28:27.837
[SLIME SQUISHING]

28:30.039 --> 28:31.080
HEY, COME ON!

28:31.080 --> 28:33.012
BEN, WE NEED A HAND.
I NEED A HAND.

28:33.012 --> 28:33.983
SAM, SAM--
HOLD ON!

28:33.983 --> 28:35.284
IT'S GOT BEN,
IT'S GOT BEN!
WHAT?!

28:35.284 --> 28:37.917
HE CAN'T BREATHE!

28:38.848 --> 28:39.789
HURRY UP, HURRY UP!

28:39.789 --> 28:42.251
HOLD ON, LET ME GET
THE VESSEL!

28:43.292 --> 28:46.025
[GRUNTING]

28:59.138 --> 29:01.140
[PANTING]

29:01.140 --> 29:02.772
IS HE ALL RIGHT?

29:02.772 --> 29:03.773
BEN, BREATHE.

29:03.773 --> 29:05.945
BREATHE, BUDDY,
TAKE A BREATH.

29:05.945 --> 29:07.917
[COUGHS]

29:07.917 --> 29:09.078
OH.

29:09.078 --> 29:11.951
[COUGHING]

29:13.923 --> 29:16.786
IS THAT USED
KITTY LITTER?

29:16.786 --> 29:17.086
UH-HUH.

29:17.086 --> 29:21.060
YOU SHOULD HAVE JUST
LET THAT THING KILL ME.

29:21.931 --> 29:24.393
YEAH, RIGHT.

29:35.504 --> 29:38.247
[GROANING]

29:42.251 --> 29:44.283
OH, GOD.

29:45.214 --> 29:48.918
OH, UH, SORRY, SAM.

29:48.918 --> 29:50.219
YOU'RE, UH,
IN KINDA LATE.

29:50.219 --> 29:54.063
YEAH, YEAH, IT'S BEEN
ONE OF THOSE NIGHTS.

29:54.063 --> 29:55.124
WHAT'S UP?

29:55.124 --> 29:57.126
WELL, I WAS
JUST WONDERING
IF YOU HAD A CHANCE

29:57.126 --> 30:00.229
TO ASK THE DEVIL
ABOUT, YOU KNOW,
WHAT WE TALKED ABOUT,

30:00.229 --> 30:01.130
GETTING A MEETING
WITH HIM.

30:01.130 --> 30:03.002
IT'S NOT GONNA HAPPEN.

30:03.002 --> 30:04.373
HE WAS PRETTY FIRM.

30:04.373 --> 30:06.435
[SIGHS]

30:06.435 --> 30:09.308
HE WON'T MEET ME
FOR 5 MINUTES?

30:09.308 --> 30:10.940
NO.

30:11.981 --> 30:14.183
THAT'S NOT RIGHT.

30:15.014 --> 30:18.247
I MEAN, THAT ISN'T FAIR.

30:19.518 --> 30:21.150
HE CAN'T DO THIS!
THE DEVIL CAN'T DO THAT!

30:21.150 --> 30:23.352
HE--I DESERVE
THE CHANCE,
JUST ONCE CHANCE--

30:23.352 --> 30:25.294
DAD...

30:26.095 --> 30:27.296
I'M SORRY, SAM.

30:27.296 --> 30:29.929
I JUST WANT
TO HELP YOU,
THAT'S ALL.

30:29.929 --> 30:33.963
I DIDN'T KNOW IT WAS
THAT IMPORTANT TO YOU.

30:33.963 --> 30:35.204
OF COURSE IT IS.

30:35.204 --> 30:37.306
YOU'RE MY SON.

30:37.306 --> 30:41.040
I'M PRETTY SURE
YOU CAN'T MEET WITH HIM.

30:41.040 --> 30:41.941
UM...

30:41.941 --> 30:43.943
BUT YOU CAN LOOK
AT THE CONTRACT,
IF YOU WANT.

30:43.943 --> 30:46.475
YEAH. OF COURSE
I WANT TO, SAM.

30:46.475 --> 30:47.877
YEAH.
SURE.

30:47.877 --> 30:49.178
YOU KNOW, I WENT
TO CATHOLIC SCHOOL,

30:49.178 --> 30:50.549
I KNOW A LITTLE BIT
OF LATIN.

30:50.549 --> 30:51.850
I, UH, LET ME DO THIS.

30:51.850 --> 30:55.154
I WILL DEDICATE
MYSELF TO FINDING
A WAY OUT OF THIS.

30:55.154 --> 30:55.925
I PROMISE.

30:55.925 --> 30:58.257
I MEAN, MAYBE
THERE'S A LOOPHOLE.

31:00.259 --> 31:02.091
[BOTH GRUNTING]

31:02.091 --> 31:05.164
THANK YOU. I WILL NOT
LET YOU DOWN.

31:06.966 --> 31:09.468
[DOOR OPENS, CLOSES]

31:17.476 --> 31:19.548
NICE SWEATER, WEIRDO.

31:20.379 --> 31:21.480
UH...

31:21.480 --> 31:23.182
WHERE ARE THE OTHER
MENTAL MIDGETS?

31:23.182 --> 31:24.984
THEY NEED
TO SIGN THESE, TOO.

31:24.984 --> 31:26.015
I DON'T KNOW.

31:26.015 --> 31:26.986
YOU ARE SOME BUNCH.

31:26.986 --> 31:29.558
THE ONE TIME
I WANT SOCK HERE,
HE'S NOT HERE.

31:29.558 --> 31:31.290
[CELL PHONE RINGS]

31:31.290 --> 31:32.261
HELLO?

31:32.261 --> 31:34.463
HEY, WHAT'S UP?

31:34.463 --> 31:37.226
YEAH, I'M FREE.

31:37.226 --> 31:39.198
NO, I HAVE NOT SEEN
THE MOVIE YET.

31:39.198 --> 31:41.330
YOU GONNA BRING GREG?

31:41.330 --> 31:42.201
[CHUCKLES]

31:42.201 --> 31:43.432
THAT SOUNDS
LIKE FUN.

31:43.432 --> 31:47.306
YEAH, I THINK I CAN
SCROUNGE UP A DATE.

31:47.306 --> 31:48.207
OK.

31:48.207 --> 31:50.309
I'LL SEE YOU
TONIGHT.

31:50.309 --> 31:51.981
LATER.

31:52.341 --> 31:54.283
THAT WAS ANDI?

31:54.283 --> 31:55.114
YEP.

31:55.114 --> 31:57.416
YOU TWO ARE GOING ON
A DOUBLE DATE.

31:57.416 --> 31:59.348
YOU AND HER,
HER AND GREG,

31:59.348 --> 32:02.551
GOIN' OUT WITH GREG.

32:02.551 --> 32:04.693
YEAH.

32:07.126 --> 32:08.457
I THINK HE'S GOOD
FOR HER.

32:08.457 --> 32:10.559
YEAH. HE'S GOOD.

32:10.559 --> 32:13.232
NICE, STABLE INFLUENCE.

32:14.003 --> 32:15.034
I THINK THEY MAKE
A CUTE COUPLE.

32:15.034 --> 32:16.435
YEAH, WELL, YOU KNOW,
GREG'S DATING TWINS, OK?

32:16.435 --> 32:18.267
2 SLUTTY TWINS,
IF YOU WANNA KNOW!

32:18.267 --> 32:20.009
WHAT?!

32:20.009 --> 32:21.240
YEAH.

32:21.240 --> 32:22.271
NEVER MIND. I DON'T KNOW.

32:22.271 --> 32:25.014
JUST FORGET IT.
FORGET IT, I'M SORRY.

32:25.014 --> 32:26.375
DON'T TELL ANDI.

32:26.375 --> 32:27.316
DON'T TELL ANDI?!

32:27.316 --> 32:29.218
YEAH, DON'T TELL ANDI.
IS IT TRUE?

32:29.218 --> 32:31.520
I DON'T--MAYBE.
I--I SAW PICTURES.

32:31.520 --> 32:33.322
HOW AM I SUPPOSED
TO NOT TELL ANDI?

32:33.322 --> 32:35.624
I MEAN, WHAT IF
THEY GET SERIOUS?

32:35.624 --> 32:37.226
AAHH!

32:37.226 --> 32:39.258
AAAH! DAMN.

32:39.258 --> 32:41.030
OH, OK.

32:47.066 --> 32:51.300
WOW, THAT'S...ABSORBENT.

32:52.301 --> 32:54.173
KNOCK, KNOCK.

32:54.173 --> 32:56.345
IT'S ABOUT TIME.
WHERE HAVE YOU BEEN?

32:56.345 --> 32:57.346
UH, JUST READING.

32:57.346 --> 33:00.679
ENGROSSED IN, UH,
READING THE OLD
NEWSPAPER.

33:00.679 --> 33:01.310
SO INTERESTING.

33:01.310 --> 33:04.683
YOU FINALLY BOUGHT A NEWSPAPER
FOR ONCE IN YOUR LIFE. SO?

33:04.683 --> 33:07.586
YEAH, TODAY--TODAY'S
PAPER, ACTUALLY.

33:07.586 --> 33:08.687
THE PAPIER DU JOUR.

33:08.687 --> 33:10.289
BIG STEAMING PILE
OF NEWS.

33:10.289 --> 33:13.692
SOMEONE'S CONTINUING
THE LAWSUIT AGAINST
BOBBY HARTFORD?

33:13.692 --> 33:15.124
YEAH. A NEW LAWYER SIGNED ON.

33:15.124 --> 33:16.695
GWYNNE GILFORD.
SHE'S A REAL PIT BULL, TOO.

33:16.695 --> 33:20.129
HARTFORD'S POLITICAL CAREER
WILL END BEFORE
IT'S EVEN STARTED.

33:20.129 --> 33:21.600
TOO BAD.

33:25.374 --> 33:28.777
THAT'S IT,
THIS IS THE ADDRESS.

33:28.777 --> 33:30.309
YEAH.

33:30.309 --> 33:32.311
OH.

33:32.311 --> 33:34.012
THAT MUST BE
THE NEW LAWYER.

33:34.012 --> 33:35.744
Sock: OH, MY GOD.

33:35.744 --> 33:37.086
YEAH.

33:37.086 --> 33:38.117
I KINDA WANT
TO BREAK THE LAW

33:38.117 --> 33:40.389
SO SHE CAN GET ALL LEGAL
ON ME, KNOW WHAT I MEAN?

33:40.389 --> 33:41.220
MM-HMM.

33:41.220 --> 33:43.422
ALL RIGHT, SO WHAT
DO WE DO? WE WARN HER?

33:43.422 --> 33:44.323
HUH?

33:44.323 --> 33:45.354
WE TELL HER WHAT,
SOME SLIME GUY

33:45.354 --> 33:46.725
IS KILLING EVERYBODY
ON THE CASE?

33:46.725 --> 33:48.657
WE'RE GONNA LOOK INSANE.

33:48.657 --> 33:49.628
YEAH.

33:49.628 --> 33:51.260
OK, LOOK, THERE SHE GOES.

33:51.260 --> 33:51.600
LOOK.
HMM.

33:51.600 --> 33:54.503
I IMAGINE A NICE LONG SHOWER
WILL BE IN ORDER.

33:54.503 --> 33:55.764
YEAH.

33:55.764 --> 33:58.367
WASH THAT VERY DIRTY
LITTLE BODY.

33:58.367 --> 34:00.069
YOU ARE DIRTY, GWYNNE.

34:00.069 --> 34:01.210
IT'S HARTFORD,
HE'S IN THE WATER SYSTEM.

34:01.210 --> 34:02.611
HE'S ALREADY IN THERE,
COME ON!

34:02.611 --> 34:04.413
WHAT?
HUH?

34:13.322 --> 34:16.155
[SHOWER RUNNING]

34:19.128 --> 34:20.729
THIS IS SO WRONG.

34:20.729 --> 34:23.532
WRONG IN ALL
THE RIGHT WAYS,
MY FRIEND.

34:23.532 --> 34:25.534
SHE'S GONNA FREAK OUT.

34:25.534 --> 34:27.266
[SCREAMS]
UH...

34:27.266 --> 34:28.337
WHO IN THE HELL
IS OUT THERE?

34:28.337 --> 34:30.169
WHO'S IN MY HOUSE?

34:30.169 --> 34:31.470
WE'RE FROM
THE WATER COMPANY,

34:31.470 --> 34:34.373
AND THERE MIGHT
BE A PROBLEM
WITH YOUR WATER.

34:34.373 --> 34:36.205
YOU HAVE NO RIGHT
TO BE IN HERE.

34:36.205 --> 34:37.676
WHAT PROBLEM WITH WATER?

34:37.676 --> 34:39.708
UH, TAINTED.
TAINTED WATER.

34:39.708 --> 34:41.650
STEP OUT
OF THE SHOWER, PLEASE.

34:41.650 --> 34:44.483
[LAUGHS]
I AM NOT COMING
OUT OF THE SHOWER.

34:44.483 --> 34:46.855
I WANT YOUR NAMES,
I'M CALLING THE POLICE.

34:46.855 --> 34:50.389
WHAT--WHAT THE...
HELL IS THIS STUFF?

34:50.389 --> 34:53.262
[SCREAMS]

34:53.262 --> 34:54.823
DIE! DIE! DIE!

34:54.823 --> 34:56.595
WHOA!

34:56.595 --> 34:59.498
GO, SAM!

35:04.803 --> 35:07.336
IT WENT DOWN THE DRAIN.

35:07.336 --> 35:09.408
BACK TO THE SEWERS!
OK!

35:09.408 --> 35:10.409
OH!

35:10.409 --> 35:13.282
YOU CAN SUE ME ANYTIME.

35:13.282 --> 35:15.314
ANYTIME!

35:17.286 --> 35:18.687
HOW THE HELL
ARE WE GONNA FIND IT?

35:18.687 --> 35:20.549
WELL, IT'S GOTTA BE
IN THE PIPES!

35:20.549 --> 35:21.420
I HEAR IT!

35:21.420 --> 35:23.892
[SLIME SQUISHING]
IT'S IN HERE, IT'S IN HERE!

35:23.892 --> 35:25.424
[ALL YELLING]

35:25.424 --> 35:30.329
HERE, TAKE THIS.
[YELLING]

35:33.262 --> 35:35.904
I NEED THE VESSEL!
I NEED THE SWEATER!

35:35.904 --> 35:37.906
[YELLING]

35:46.175 --> 35:47.376
DO YOU THINK SAM IS OK?

35:47.376 --> 35:49.778
HE'S PROBABLY GOOD,
RIGHT?

35:49.778 --> 35:51.380
SAM!

35:51.380 --> 35:54.223
SAM!

35:56.855 --> 35:59.528
DUDE, GO, GO!

35:59.858 --> 36:03.332
CHRISTMAS COME EARLY
THIS YEAR, BOBBY!

36:07.496 --> 36:10.239
[GRUNTING]

36:12.371 --> 36:14.703
[GROANING]

36:15.544 --> 36:16.945
WE GET HIM?

36:16.945 --> 36:18.777
WE GET HIM?
WE GOT HIM?

36:18.777 --> 36:19.908
YEAH!
YES!

36:19.908 --> 36:21.610
YOU SAVED MY LIFE!

36:21.610 --> 36:23.382
I ALMOST LOST IT,
I COULDN'T BREATHE!

36:23.382 --> 36:25.814
I KNOW. I JUMPED IN THERE
AND NAILED THAT DUDE!

36:25.814 --> 36:26.955
WE GOT HIM!

36:26.955 --> 36:29.418
[ALL LAUGHING]

36:29.418 --> 36:30.889
WE DID IT! YES!

36:30.889 --> 36:33.322
YOU CAN LET GO.

36:33.322 --> 36:35.294
I CAN'T MOVE MY ARMS.

36:35.294 --> 36:36.725
WHAT?
I CAN'T--

36:36.725 --> 36:38.867
IT'S LIKE THE SLIME
CRUSTED UP
IN THE SLEEVES,

36:38.867 --> 36:42.731
IT'S LIKE CONCRETE!
I CAN'T LET GO.

36:43.932 --> 36:46.905
WELL, WHAT THE HELL
ARE WE GOING TO DO?

36:49.908 --> 36:51.480
Ben: UH, EXCUSE ME,
EXCUSE ME, I'M SO SORRY.

36:51.480 --> 36:53.882
THANK YOU. WE'RE JUST GOING
TO COME THROUGH RIGHT HERE.

36:53.882 --> 36:56.815
EXCUSE ME.
I'M SO SORRY ABOUT THAT.

36:56.815 --> 36:57.246
EXCUSE ME.

36:57.246 --> 37:00.249
YEAH, I'M HERE FOR
MY FRIEND, ALL RIGHT?

37:00.249 --> 37:01.250
HE'S NEEDY.

37:01.250 --> 37:02.891
TAKE A PICTURE. GOD.

37:02.891 --> 37:04.222
OOOH.

37:04.222 --> 37:05.824
HI, GLADYS.

37:05.824 --> 37:07.626
UM...

37:07.626 --> 37:09.798
VESSEL DROP-OFF?

37:09.798 --> 37:12.361
PLACE THE VESSEL
ON THE MAT.

37:12.361 --> 37:15.003
UM, WE CAN'T
GET IT OFF.

37:15.003 --> 37:17.806
YOU NEED AN EXTRACTION?

37:20.539 --> 37:21.940
DON'T WORRY.

37:21.940 --> 37:24.313
HARDLY EVER HURT ANYONE.

37:24.313 --> 37:27.546
I DON'T KNOW WHAT THE HELL
THAT'S ALL ABOUT.

37:27.546 --> 37:30.248
ENTER THERE, PLEASE.

37:36.785 --> 37:38.357
HEY, SAM.

37:38.357 --> 37:39.888
HEY, HOW ARE YOU?

37:39.888 --> 37:41.390
SLUTTY TWINS?

37:41.390 --> 37:45.334
YOU TOLD JOSIE THAT GREG
WAS DATING SLUTTY TWINS.

37:45.334 --> 37:46.295
OH.

37:46.295 --> 37:48.737
JOSIE TOLD YOU, HUH?
YEAH.

37:48.737 --> 37:50.869
WHAT, THESE ONES?

37:52.301 --> 37:53.902
YEAH, YEAH,
THOSE ARE THE ONES.

37:53.902 --> 37:54.803
THEY'RE HIS SISTERS.

37:54.803 --> 37:58.877
GOD, WHAT WOULD POSSESS YOU
TO SAY SOMETHING LIKE THAT?

37:58.877 --> 38:00.349
OH, I'M SORRY.

38:00.349 --> 38:01.780
I JUST...

38:01.780 --> 38:03.712
SOMEONE GAVE ME
THE WRONG INFORMATION.

38:03.712 --> 38:04.653
WHO?

38:04.653 --> 38:06.585
WHO WOULD SAY THAT?

38:06.585 --> 38:08.317
I...

38:09.688 --> 38:11.560
I CAN'T--
I CAN'T REMEMBER.

38:11.560 --> 38:13.422
MM-HMM. ANOTHER ONE
OF YOUR BIG SECRETS, HUH?

38:13.422 --> 38:16.795
YOU KNOW WHAT?
YOU WANT ME TO STAY
OUT OF YOUR PRIVATE LIFE?

38:16.795 --> 38:18.827
FINE. STAY OUT OF MINE,
GOT IT?

38:18.827 --> 38:23.472
WHOA, ANDI, HOLD ON!
IT WAS A MISTAKE!

38:32.381 --> 38:34.583
HEY, SAMMY.

38:34.583 --> 38:36.415
FEEL LIKE A GAME?

38:36.415 --> 38:38.917
[SIGHS]

38:40.619 --> 38:42.891
YOU SET ME UP.

38:42.891 --> 38:44.322
I DID.

38:44.322 --> 38:45.554
BUT I FEEL AWFUL
ABOUT IT.

38:45.554 --> 38:47.726
NO, YOU DON'T.
YOU DID IT ON PURPOSE
TO SCREW ME,

38:47.726 --> 38:50.599
TO MAKE ME LOOK LIKE
A SCUMBAG IN FRONT OF ANDI.

38:50.599 --> 38:51.329
COME ON.

38:51.329 --> 38:52.601
I THOUGHT YOU WERE
MISTER HIGH ROAD.

38:52.601 --> 38:57.335
"OH, I'M NOT GOING TO BE
TEMPTED BY PICTURES OF GREG
WITH SLUTTY TWINS."

38:57.335 --> 38:59.067
AND THEN WHEN
THE CHIPS WERE DOWN,

38:59.067 --> 39:00.669
YOU SPILLED YOUR GUTS.

39:00.669 --> 39:02.411
YEAH, WELL,
I WAS BEING STUPID.

39:02.411 --> 39:02.911
MAN TO MAN?

39:02.911 --> 39:08.076
YOU ALWAYS GET A LITTLE STUPID
AROUND THAT GIRL, SAM.

39:08.076 --> 39:08.877
[SIGHS]

39:08.877 --> 39:12.120
LET ME MAKE ONE THING
PERFECTLY CLEAR.

39:13.382 --> 39:16.985
I KNOW WHAT
YOU WERE PLANNING.

39:17.386 --> 39:18.627
YOU WERE GOING
TO TELL ANDI

39:18.627 --> 39:20.459
ALL ABOUT OUR LITTLE
ARRANGEMENT.

39:20.459 --> 39:22.991
WELL, THAT JUST
CAN'T HAPPEN.

39:23.462 --> 39:25.093
THAT WOULD BE BAD
FOR YOU.

39:25.093 --> 39:28.737
AND VERY BAD FOR ANDI.

39:30.068 --> 39:31.139
USUALLY IT DOESN'T
END WELL

39:31.139 --> 39:35.103
FOR THOSE MORTALS
THAT COME ONTO MY RADAR.

39:35.103 --> 39:37.075
YOUR FOLKS, YOU,

39:37.075 --> 39:38.076
SOCK AND BEN.

39:38.076 --> 39:39.648
SOCK AND BEN ARE FINE.

39:39.648 --> 39:41.410
FOR NOW.

39:41.680 --> 39:46.114
BUT YOUR SECRET DIES
WITH YOU, YOUR FAMILY
AND YOUR FRIENDS.

39:46.114 --> 39:48.417
IT DIES.

39:48.417 --> 39:50.559
UNDERSTAND?

39:51.590 --> 39:53.121
I'M JUST SAYING,
YOU KNOW,

39:53.121 --> 39:55.163
YOU OUGHT TO THINK
LONG AND HARD

39:55.163 --> 40:00.068
BEFORE YOU INVITE ANDI
INTO OUR LITTLE CIRCLE.

40:01.069 --> 40:03.432
IS THAT A THREAT?

40:03.432 --> 40:05.033
NO. NO, SAM.

40:05.033 --> 40:06.835
JUST THE TRUTH.

40:06.835 --> 40:08.907
SO I'M NEVER GOING
TO BE WITH ANDI,

40:08.907 --> 40:10.839
THAT'S WHAT YOU'RE SAYING?

40:10.839 --> 40:11.910
WHAT? NO.

40:11.910 --> 40:14.042
HEY, WHY WOULD I
DENY YOU THE LOVE
OF YOUR LIFE?

40:14.042 --> 40:17.446
I'M JUST SAYING,
YOU'RE GOING TO WANT
TO KEEP HER SAFE,

40:17.446 --> 40:19.087
AND IF THAT MEANS...

40:19.087 --> 40:24.593
TELLING A LITTLE LIE
OR TWO, SO BE IT.

40:24.593 --> 40:28.426
I'M JUST LOOKING AFTER
YOU TWO LOVEBIRDS.

40:30.158 --> 40:30.929
OH.

40:30.929 --> 40:33.061
DON'T FEEL SO BAD ABOUT
KEEPING A SECRET.

40:33.061 --> 40:36.104
THAT'S WHAT PEOPLE DO,
ALL THE TIME.

40:36.104 --> 40:38.166
THROUGHOUT
HUMAN HISTORY.

40:38.166 --> 40:43.171
IT'S NOBEL TO PROTECT
THE ONES YOU LOVE, SAM.

40:43.872 --> 40:46.545
IF YOU REALLY CARE
ABOUT SOMEONE...

40:46.545 --> 40:50.448
SOMETIMES IT'S SAFER

40:50.448 --> 40:53.181
TO KEEP THEM IN THE DARK.
